"title": "5293: defence, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5293",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's people are to defend the needy and those in their care. They are also to defend the truth entrusted to them.</p>\n<h2>Defence of the needy</h2>\n<h3>God commands his people to defend the needy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:8-Prov31:9\">PRO 31:8–31:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:17\">ISA 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:2\">ISA 10:1–10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:6–58:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:9-Isa58:10\">ISA 58:9–58:10</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those who defended the needy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:4\">PSA 72:4</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:17\">EXO 2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:24\">ACT 7:24</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:15-Ruth2:16\">RUT 2:15–2:16</a> <em>Boaz</em></p>\n<h3>Neglect of the cause of the needy is condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:2-Ps82:4\">PSA 82:2–82:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:4\">JOB 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:23-Isa1:24\">ISA 1:23–1:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:20-Isa29:21\">ISA 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:26-Jer5:29\">JER 5:26–5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:15-Jer22:17\">JER 22:15–22:17</a></p>\n<h2>Church leaders are to defend the flock of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:28–20:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:10-Titus1:11\">TIT 1:10–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are urged to defend the faith</h2>\n<h3>It is the responsibility of all believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:27-Phil1:28\">PHP 1:27–1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:15\">2TH 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>It is the responsibility of Christian leaders in particular</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:13-2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:3-1Tim1:10\">1TI 1:3–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:12-Titus1:14\">TIT 1:12–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of leaders who defended the faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:16\">PHP 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:8-Acts6:10\">ACT 6:8–6:10</a> <em>Stephen</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:27-Acts18:28\">ACT 18:27–18:28</a> <em>Apollos</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6-Gal1:9\">GAL 1:6–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11-Gal2:14\">GAL 2:11–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:7\">PHP 1:7</a></p>",
